NAME
  vdlimit - manage context disk limits
SYNOPSIS
  vdlimit [-AGRS] [-l lim] [-x xid] [mountpoint]
DESCRIPTION
  vdlimit is used to set disk space limits for the given context id.
OPTIONS
  Commands  
    -A       Add disk limit entry for mountpoint
    -G       Get disk limit for mountpoint
    -R       Remove disk limit entry for mountpoint
    -S       Set disk limit entry for mountpoint

  Options  
    -l lim   Set limit described in lim (see DISK LIMIT FORMAT STRING)
    -x xid   Context ID
DISK LIMIT FORMAT STRING
    lim = <SU>,<SM>,<IU>,<IM>,<RR> where
        SU  is the used space in kbytes,
        SM  is the maximum space in kbytes,
        IU  is the used inode count,
        IM  is the maximum inode count, and
        RR  is reserved for root in percent.
EXAMPLE
  Add a disk limit entry to /vserver/myvps for context '123':

      $ vdlimit -A -x 123 /vservers/myvps

  Set max space to 500M on the entry created above:

      $ vdlimit -S -l ,512000,,,, -x 123 /vservers/myvps
